cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as language modeling. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes methods to reduce the number of parameters and accelerate training of LSTM networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as LSTM networks are commonly used in AI applications. It may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural networks, and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as LSTM networks are also used in image and video processing tasks.
